body:
I&#039;ve been thinking of an idea that might help new players, keep in mind this idea probably won&#039;t help more skilled players.

When a player dies, while on the death screen, a tip about the source of death displays at the top of the screen.

When new players die in league, then probably don&#039;t understand why they died. My first idea is in the death screen, to display a tip to deal with the champion that killed them. For example, &quot;_Riven is a very strong 1v1 champion, but if you silence her she looses a huge portion of the damage she could have dealt to you_&quot;. If a player dies to a turret, a tip like &quot;_Turrets deal a huge amount of damage, stay behind your minions to avoid turret damage_.&quot;
